cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.DB 

This paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques for building explainable recommender systems. The paper focuses on the use of Knowledge Graphs to provide explanations to users. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also discusses the use of Semantics-Aware Autoencoder, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of databases to store and retrieve information, which falls under the category of cs.DB (Databases). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of different types of information on the explanatory criteria, which falls under the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
